re, Ireland","First wife of Turlogh Mor":"Mor, Chuuk, Micronesia","nameMeanings":[{"name":"OBrien","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Dermot, Liam, Brigid, Declan, Donovan, John Patrick, Kieran, Colm, Donal, Brennan, Caitlin.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Briain</b> ‘descendant of <i>Brian</i>’, a personal name probably based on the element <i>bre-</i> ‘hill’, with the transferred sense ‘eminence’, i.e. ‘exalted one’. See also   Bryan  . In Ireland there has also been some confusion with   O'Byrne   (see   Byrne  ).","History: This name is borne in particular by one of the greatest of Irish septs, descendants of Brian Boru, who rose to the high kingship of Ireland in 1002."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Brion","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish William Kevin.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"Bryan","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Bryant  .","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of <b>Ó Briain</b>, see   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Briant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  , with excrescent <i>-t</i>."]},{"name":"O'Bryant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"McBrien","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Seamus.","Irish:","Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Briain</b> ‘son of Brian’. See   O'Brien   and   Bryan  ."]},{"name":"O'Brian","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish James Patrick, Padraic.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]}]},{"name":"Conor","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of   Conchobhar ."],"variants":[{"name":"Connor","meanings":["Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Conchobhar . In recent years the name has also become very popular outside Ireland."]},{"name":"Conchobhar","meanings":["Traditional name, probably meaning ‘lover of hounds’; borne by a legendary king of Ulster who lived at the time of Christ."]}]},{"name":"Conchobar","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name, probably meaning ‘lover of hounds’; borne by a legendary king of Ulster who lived at the time of Christ."],"variants":[{"name":"Cnochúr","meanings":["Modern Gaelic form of   Conchobhar ."]},{"name":"Conor","meanings":["Anglicized form of   Conchobhar ."]},{"name":"Connor","meanings":["Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Conchobhar . In recent years the name has also become very popular outside Ireland."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Conor Conchobar OBrien was born about 1265, in Thomond, County Clare, Ireland, his father, Toirdhealbhach Mór Ó Briain, King of Thomond, was 21 and his mother, Sadhbh Mac Carthy, was 12. He had at least 2 daughters with Sabina O'Kennedy. He died on 19 July 1329, in Battle, Camrose County No. 22, Alberta, Canada, at the age of 65."},"et":{"ABT 1265–19 Jul 1329":"umbes 1265–19. juuli 1329","1265–1329":"1265–1329","1290–1311":"1290–1311","–1311":"–1311","1267–Female":"1267–Surnud","1285–1344":"1285–1344","1303–1344":"1303–1344","1245–1306":"1245–1306","1255–Female":"1255–Surnud","19 Jul 1329":"19. juuli 1329","1285":"1285","1290":"1290","1303":"1303","ABT 1265":"umbes 1265","1245":"1245","1344":"1344","1267":"1267","1311":"1311","1255":"1255","1265":"1265","1329":"1329","1306":"1306","Thomond, North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"Thomond, County Clare, Iirimaa","Ennis, Clare, Munster, Ireland":"Ennis, County Clare, Iirimaa","Battle of Thurles (Slain)":"Battle, Camrose County No. 22, Alberta, Kanada","North Munster, Clare, Ireland":"County Clare, Iirimaa","First wife of Turlogh Mor":"Mor, Chuuk, Mikroneesia"},"fi":{"ABT 1265–19 Jul 1329":"noin 1265–19.